The history array entries should include a type annotation or interface definition to ensure consistency across the codebase. Currently, the structure is defined inline with no validation. Consider creating an interface like:

interface HistoryEntry {
    event: string;
    timestamp: string;
}

This would provide type safety and make it clear what properties are expected in history entries, especially if different event types need different properties in the future.

The sessions title element is made clickable with cursor: pointer and a click handler, but it lacks proper accessibility attributes and keyboard support. Based on patterns in the codebase (e.g., chatAttachmentsContentPart.ts:85-111, chatSuggestNextWidget.ts:109-170), clickable elements should include:
1. `role="button"` attribute to indicate the element is interactive
2. `tabindex="0"` to make it keyboard focusable
3. An appropriate `aria-label` attribute for screen readers
4. Keyboard event handler for Enter and Space keys to trigger the action

Without these attributes, keyboard users and screen reader users cannot access this functionality.
