The duplicate handling has a collision bug. When a duplicate heading is found, the generated slug with the numeric suffix is not tracked in the entries map. This causes collisions when a heading naturally matches a generated duplicate slug. For example: headings "Header", "Header", "Header-1" would result in both the second "Header" and "Header-1" getting the id "header-1". The generated slugs should be added to the entries map to prevent such collisions.
```suggestion
				let slugValue = slug.value;
				let count = 0;
				let uniqueSlugValue = slugValue;

				if (entries.has(slugValue)) {
					count = entries.get(slugValue)!.count + 1;
					uniqueSlugValue = `${slugValue}-${count}`;
					// Find the next available unique slug
					while (entries.has(uniqueSlugValue)) {
						count++;
						uniqueSlugValue = `${slugValue}-${count}`;
					}
					entries.get(slugValue)!.count = count;
					entries.set(uniqueSlugValue, { count: 0 });
					return this.fromHeading(uniqueSlugValue);
				}

