The `certificate-error` event handler has an incorrect signature. According to Electron's API, this event provides additional parameters: `event`, `webContents`, `url`, `error`, `certificate`, and `callback`. The event object doesn't have a `preventDefault()` method. Instead, you should call `event.preventDefault()` and then call the `callback` with `true` to trust the certificate or `false` to reject it:

```typescript
.on('certificate-error', (event, webContents, url, error, certificate, callback) => {
	event.preventDefault();
	callback(false);
})
```

Passing `false` to the callback will reject the certificate and prevent the page from loading with certificate errors.
```suggestion
			.on('certificate-error', (event, webContents, url, error, certificate, callback) => {
				event.preventDefault();
				callback(false);
			});
```

